<p>From now on we don't need to remember the issue number anymore! Executing</p>

<pre><code>$ git commit -m"Introduced new property in configuration file \ 
to define default (global) transaction mode" 
</code></pre>

<p>will result with <code>[ARQ-1186] Introduced new property in configuration file to define default (global) transaction mode</code> as commit message. Life is so easier now ;)</p>

<p><em><strong>Note:</strong> If you are using Eclipse git integration this approach won't work. EGit is not aware of commit hooks.</em></p>
